v0.1.19_Ingredient_Delete_Foundation
Date
2026-06-10
Summary
Aligned Ingredient deletion architecture with Recipe deletion architecture by introducing soft delete support and deleted-state tracking.
This commit establishes the foundation for future inactive vs deleted behavior across all composition domains.
________________________________________
Completed
Ingredient Soft Delete Foundation
Added:
deleted boolean not null default false
to:
public.ing_items
Result:
Ingredients now support:
active = true,  deleted = false
    Available

active = false, deleted = false
    Inactive / Temporarily unavailable

deleted = true
    Deleted / Permanently unavailable
________________________________________
Ingredient View Update
Updated:
public.vw_ing_items
Added:
deleted
to the published view output.
Column added as final column to preserve existing view compatibility.
________________________________________
Ingredient List Filtering
Updated:
getIngredients
Deleted ingredients are now excluded from Ingredient List.
Pattern:
coalesce(deleted, false) = false
________________________________________
Ingredient Delete Behavior
Replaced hard delete behavior.
Previous:
delete from ing_items
New:
update ing_items
set
  active = false,
  deleted = true
Ingredient records are now retained for future recovery.
________________________________________
Recipe Component Ingredient Picklists
Updated:
getRecComponentItems
Ingredient selection now excludes:
deleted = true
while continuing to require:
active = true
Deleted ingredients can no longer be added to new Recipes.
